  "utterances": [
    {
      "id": "u001",
      "speaker": "mara-finch",
      "type": "speech",
      "text": "Oh the Numbers are absolutely the *pulling strings* kind of future, but the show also keeps swearing it\u2019s about agency\u2014so the plot holes start the second we ask \u201cperfect lottery prediction\u201d like it\u2019s science and not mythology wearing a calculator. Because if the timelines branch, why does the channel look so deterministic\u2014like, did we just invent branching to make everyone feel better about being wrong? And I\u2019m gonna ask you the annoying question: are the Numbers an island authority thing, a Dharma instrument, or Jacob/Smokey using math as a puppet master?",
